ENTRY       EC 1.1.3.41                 Enzyme
NAME        alditol oxidase;
            xylitol oxidase;
            xylitol:oxygen oxidoreductase;
            AldO
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
            With oxygen as acceptor
SYSNAME     alditol:oxygen oxidoreductase
REACTION    an alditol + O2 = an aldose + H2O2 [RN:R07152]
ALL_REAC    R07152
SUBSTRATE   alditol [CPD:C00717];
            O2 [CPD:C00007]
PRODUCT     aldose [CPD:C01370];
            H2O2 [CPD:C00027]
COMMENT     The enzyme from Streptomyces sp. IKD472 and from Streptomyces coelicolor is a monomeric oxidase containing one molecule of FAD per molecule of protein [1,2]. While xylitol (five carbons) and sorbitol (6 carbons) are the preferred substrates, other alditols, including L-threitol (four carbons), D-arabitol (five carbons), D-galactitol (six carbons) and D-mannitol (six carbons) can also act as substrates, but more slowly [1,2]. Belongs in the vanillyl-alcohol-oxidase family of enzymes [2].
